last_episode_to_air.name: Woe To Wo Fat
last_episode_to_air.overview: The series concludes with the final showdown between McGarrett and Wo Fat. Three scientists have gone missing. They have one thing in common: they all attended a symposium that discussed a possible space-based, laser defense system. McGarrett impersonates a fourth scientist, Dr. Elton Raintree, who attended the same gathering and is soon abducted. Wo Fat is behind it all and wants the scientists to complete their work and produce such a device.

name: Hawaii Five-O
overview: Hawaii Five-O is an American police procedural drama series produced by CBS Productions and Leonard Freeman. Set in Hawaii, the show originally aired for 12 seasons from 1968 to 1980, and continues in reruns. Jack Lord portrayed Detective Lieutenant Steve McGarrett, the head of a special state police task force which was based on an actual unit that existed under martial law in the 1940s. The theme music composed by Morton Stevens became especially popular. Many episodes would end with McGarrett instructing his subordinate to "Book 'em, Danno!", sometimes specifying a charge such as "murder one".

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: The first season of Hawaii Five-O, an American television series, began September 20, 1968, and ended on March 19, 1969. It aired on CBS. The region 1 DVD was released on March 6, 2007.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: The second season of Hawaii Five-O, an American television series, began September 24, 1969, and ended on March 11, 1970. It aired on CBS. The region 1 DVD was released on July 31, 2007.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: The third season of Hawaii Five-O, an American television series, began September 16, 1970, and ended on March 10, 1971. It aired on CBS. The region 1 DVD was released on January 22, 2008.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: The fourth season of Hawaii Five-O, an American television series, began September 14, 1971, and ended on March 7, 1972. It aired on CBS. The region 1 DVD was released on June 10, 2008.

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview: The fifth season of Hawaii Five-O premiered on September 12, 1972 and ended March 13, 1973. 24 episodes aired during this season. The Region 1 DVD was released on November 18, 2008.

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview:
The sixth season of Hawaii Five-O premiered on September 11, 1973 and ended February 26, 1974. 24 episodes aired during this season. The Region 1 DVD was released on April 21, 2009.

Creator and executive producer Leonard Freeman died during this season.

episodes.name: Cocoon (1)
episodes.overview: Red Chinese agent Wo Fat uses a sensory deprivation chamber to procure information from U.S. agents. Steve McGarrett, head of Hawaii Five-O, investigates the death of a close friend who appears to have drowned. Steve's knowledge about his friend and a mysterious white substance lead him into a high-level intelligence matter involving a foreign agent.  McGarrett, head of Hawaii's state police force, poses as "control," possessor of the names of other agents. He allows himself to be captured and placed in the chamber; will he be able to withstand the torture?

episodes.name: Cocoon (2)
episodes.overview: McGarrett is caught and cocooned, and must escape this torture and shut down Wo Fat's operation.

episodes.name: Full Fathom Five
episodes.overview: Victor Reese and his wife Nora are conning rich widows out of their savings, and then poisoning them and dumping them in the ocean. McGarrett and company hatch a plan to use a female officer to trap the duo.

episodes.name: Strangers In Our Own Land
episodes.overview: Five-O probes into the death of an official who was instrumental in the development of the islands, and discovers a tangled web of lies and deception.

episodes.name: Tiger By The Tail
episodes.overview: A young singer, Bobby George, plans his own kidnapping as a stunt, but when his father offers $500,000 for his release, his co-conspirators decide to double-cross him and take the money.

episodes.name: Samurai
episodes.overview: McGarrett and the gang must simultaneously protect a gangster from Japanese assassins and also try to convict him for his underworld activities.

episodes.name: ... And They Painted Daisies On His Coffin
episodes.overview: Danny Williams is accused of shooting an apparently unarmed young boy. Meanwhile, in his investigation, McGarrett comes up against Big Chicken, a nasty dope dealer.

episodes.name: Twenty-Four Karat Kill
episodes.overview: A woman buys fish from a monger, and is followed home and murdered. McGarrett and the team must discover who killed her and stop smugglers from completing their operation.

episodes.name: The Ways Of Love
episodes.overview: After a girl dies during a high speed chase, a trail of clues leads McGarrett to a Los Angeles prison, where he must act the part of convict Steve Crowley to gain the trust of his cellmate for a break-out, which will help reveal the plans of the crime.

episodes.name: No Blue Skies
episodes.overview: When a singer, Joey Rand, finds that his career doesn't pay well enough, he turns to cat burglary. However he doesn't reckon on Hawaii Five-O.

episodes.name: By the Numbers
episodes.overview: A winning lottery ticket drags an army private into a the murky world of mob politics and vice.

episodes.name: Yesterday Died And Tomorrow Won't Be Born
episodes.overview: When McGarrett is shot and badly wounded on a beachside jog, Danno and the team must work feverishly to find the culprit and prevent him from committing any more murders.

episodes.name: Deathwatch
episodes.overview: McGarrett must protect a protect a mob underboss so he is able to testify against his superior, Joe Matsukino. However, Matsukino has many tricks up his sleeve to silence his former colleague permanentlyâ€¦

episodes.name: Pray Love Remember, Pray Love Remember
episodes.overview: When a young female student is found murdered on campus, suspicions fall on her boyfriend but McGarrett senses that something is not right.

episodes.name: King Of The Hill
episodes.overview: Danno is taken hostage by a Vietnam veteran who is suffering delusional flashbacks and sees everyone as forces sent to kill him.

episodes.name: Up Tight
episodes.overview: Young Eadie Hastings cannot be saved by Danno from jumping of a cliff, and Five-O think that she was high on speed. They track her source to a crank teacher, Professor David Stone, and Danno must pose as a surfer to investigate the drug pushers and users.

episodes.name: Face Of The Dragon
episodes.overview: A man is found dead after having been robbed by a motorcyclist with a gun, and McGarrett is shocked to discover that the man was suffering from bubonic plague. The islands are quarantined, and the team must follow a series of clues to discover the cause of the outbreak.

episodes.name: The Box
episodes.overview: Big Chicken returns in a tense prison hostage drama when McGarrett has to give himself over to the criminals as a bargaining chip and use psychology to take control of the situation.

episodes.name: One For The Money
episodes.overview:
When a girl is found murdered and numbered 

'one', McGarrett suspects a serial killer. However the killer seems to be very selective in targeting members of a particular company, and suspicion soon falls on two brothers who stand to inherit the firm from their aged aunt.

episodes.name: Along Came Joey
episodes.overview: When the boxing son of a policeman, Phil Kalama, is killed, he starts a personal vendetta, and McGarrett must both solve the crime and stop Kalama from committing another murder.

episodes.name: Once Upon A Time (1)
episodes.overview: When the son of McGarrett's sister falls ill with cancer and she becomes involved in â€˜naturology', her husband calls in Steve to investigate and persuade her to stop paying for the useless treatments. However, the quack doctor sets up a court case to prevent McGarrett from closing her practice.

episodes.name: Once Upon A Time (2)
episodes.overview: McGarrett must use all legal means possible to win the court case against Dr. C.L. Fremont, stopping her fake treatments and saving his sister from more anguish and pain.

episodes.name: Not That Much Different
episodes.overview: When a leader of a student peace movement is killed, McGarrett has to investigate the murder against a wall of silence and a distrust of the police by the activists.

episodes.name: Six Kilos
episodes.overview: Chin Ho and Dan Williams are tracking a safecracker but he pulls a gun and Danno ends up shooting him. McGarrett takes his identity of Harry Brown and must infiltrate a sophisticated gang of international thieves.

episodes.name: The Big Kahuna
episodes.overview: Sam Kalakua, a distant cousin of Kono, is being frightened into an early grave by an fake apparition of a Hawaiian god created by his nephew, who wants to sell the estate to a land merchant.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: The first season of Hawaii Five-O, an American television series, began September 20, 1968, and ended on March 19, 1969. It aired on CBS. The region 1 DVD was released on March 6, 2007.

episodes.name: A Thousand Pardons -- You're Dead!
episodes.overview: An army sergeant and a office worker have a scam in which they use bar girls to claim G.I. widow benefits, and then murder them to take the cash. McGarrett and company must use the girls to get to the core of the plot.

episodes.name: To Hell With Babe Ruth
episodes.overview: A Japanese World War II veteran, Yoshio Nagata, escapes from a mental hospital and tries to carry out his wartime orders to blow up a refinery.

episodes.name: Forty Feet High And It Kills!
episodes.overview: A tsunami warning is called and a geneticist is evacuated from a conference. He is then kidnapped under the orders of Wo Fat, but he uses his diabetic medical condition as a ploy to stop Wo Fat from carrying out the plan to return him to China.

episodes.name: Just Lucky, I Guess
episodes.overview: A middle-aged mainland hardware salesman uses a prostitute, and then witnesses her murder by a mobster. He refuses to testify because of the damage to his reputation and that he doesn't want to be involved. McGarrett must persuade him to do the right thing.

episodes.name: Savage Sunday
episodes.overview: McGarrett must interrupt his Sunday to deal with both terrorists and politics when a revolutionary group steal guns from a barracks for their overseas cause.

episodes.name: A Bullet For McGarrett
episodes.overview: A university professor, Dr. Paul Farrar, is using hypnosis to programme students into becoming assassins. McGarrett uses a policewoman as bait for Dr. Farrar, but the plan goes wrong and her life is put in danger.

episodes.name: Sweet Terror
episodes.overview: McGarrett must counter a threat by international terrorist Erich Stoss to use a fungus to wipe out Hawaii's sugar cane, half of the world's supply.

episodes.name: King Kamehameha Blues
episodes.overview: Four university students hatch a plot to steal the robes of King Kamehameha, and McGarrett and the team must apply pressure to the gang's weak point to retrieve the robes and catch the thieves.

episodes.name: The Singapore File
episodes.overview: McGarrett gets a phone call from Singapore and goes to rescue Nicole Wylie, a witness who has changed her mind and wants to testify. However, the pair must face many dangers on their return trip back to Hawaii.

episodes.name: All The King's Horses
episodes.overview: An assassination attempt on a prominent politician, Charles Irwin, leads Five-O to Mike Finney, a former racketeer who has been clean for nine years. However, Finney insists he is innocent, and the trail of clues leads right back to Irwin.

episodes.name: Leopard On The Rock
episodes.overview: When a dictator's plane is diverted to Hawaii as part of a plan to kill him, McGarrett must deal with the complex politics of the situation and protect the hated leader.

episodes.name: The Devil And Mr. Frog
episodes.overview: When a young son of a businessman escapes from captivity by â€˜The Devil' and â€˜Mr. Frog', Five-O must recover the $300,000 ransom money that the desperate father paid.

episodes.name: The Joker's Wild, Man, Wild!
episodes.overview: Two young men play an increasingly dangerous and deadly game for the attentions of a beautiful but spoiled heiress, who plays them off against each other.

episodes.name: Which Way Did They Go?
episodes.overview: A career criminal, Connors, fools McGarrett and the team into protecting the wrong bank, and robs a nearby one, taking the wife of the manager hostage. Things turn ugly when one of his goons assaults and murders her. McGarrett must race to capture Connors before he can do any more damage.

episodes.name: Blind Tiger
episodes.overview: McGarrett gets a surprise birthday party, but when he goes to pack the presents in his car, it explodes and blinds him. Danno, Chin Ho and Kono must work to catch those responsible, whilst McGarrett has to get used to not having his eyesight.

episodes.name: Bored, She Hung Herself
episodes.overview: Don Miles, a health freak, uses a hanging-type exercise to promote his wellbeing, but his girlfriend Wanda tries it, and seemingly dies in the attempt. However, all is not what it seemsâ€¦

episodes.name: Run, Johnny, Run
episodes.overview: Two military policeman spot John Mala, a man who McGarrett has helped in the past, but who has gone AWOL. One of the policemen is shot, and tensions rise as Five-O and the army police clash in their techniques of investigation and their treatment of the local population.

episodes.name: Killer Bee
episodes.overview: A psychiatric worker, George Loomis, is trying to drive a fellow Vietnam veteran Ted Frazer crazy in order to cover up the fact that he massacred his own platoon during an action. Loomis kidnaps boys and drugs Frazer to make it look like Frazer is mad and to blame for the tragedy. McGarrett and the team must unravel this web of lies and clear Frazer.

episodes.name: The One With The Gun
episodes.overview: Peter Corman is murdered during a game of poker, and his brother Lorenzo arrives in Hawaii for revenge. McGarrett must work out what happened and prevent Lorenzo from carrying out his intentions.

episodes.name: Cry, Lie
episodes.overview: Chin Ho is accused of bribery, and cannot provide alibis for the nights in question. Worse, he is called to the middle of nowhere for a set-up. Chin's position is threatened, and the Governor orders an inquiry. McGarrett and the others must work out how Chin was framed and clear him of the accusations.

episodes.name: Most Likely To Murder
episodes.overview: Lew Morgan and his wife are friends of Danno, but she is murdered, and Morgan sets out to find the culprit. However, his wife seems to be hiding secrets that may have caused her death.

episodes.name: Nightmare Road
episodes.overview: A research scientist, Dr. Royce, is set up by revolutionaries to be transported away from the islands in a submarine. McGarrett must stop this from happening and also has to contend with the interference of federal agents in the case.

episodes.name: Three Dead Cows At Makapuu (1)
episodes.overview: Dr. Alexander Kline, a biological scientist, views his work as evil, and to prove it, he plans to unleash a deadly germ that would kill thousands. Three dead cows lead McGarrett on a desperate chase to track down the toxin, involving a friendly telephone operator and top Washington agents.

episodes.name: Three Dead Cows At Makapuu (2)
episodes.overview: Dr. Kline's deadly toxin is lost, he is having second thoughts about his plan, and McGarrett has to find the vial before it disintegrates and poisons the whole island. Already the toxin is doing its deadly work as innocent people come into contact with it.

episodes.name: Kiss The Queen Goodbye
episodes.overview: Camilla Carver, a con-artist, blackmails a politician to take her to an event where she can steal the priceless Queen of Polynesia emerald and swap it for a fake. However, McGarrett and the team are at the event and make sure that neither the gem, Carver or her accomplice vanish.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: The second season of Hawaii Five-O, an American television series, began September 24, 1969, and ended on March 11, 1970. It aired on CBS. The region 1 DVD was released on July 31, 2007.

episodes.name: ... And A Time To Die
episodes.overview: Five-O must act swiftly when the daughter of a top neurosurgeon is kidnapped by Wo Fat in order to make the surgeon operate on a wounded U.S. undercover agent who is carrying secret inforrmation of use to the Chinese.

episodes.name: Trouble In Mind
episodes.overview: Singer Eadie Jordan has not only a comeback concert to perform, but also a serious heroin addiction. Poisoned heroin is being peddled on the islands, and McGarrett must try to save Eadie from scoring for the last time.

episodes.name: The Second Shot
episodes.overview: Dr. Lemira, an opposition leader for Greece, is living in exile in Hawaii, but Klaus Marberg is sent to assassinate him. His plan is to get himself shot and work his way into Dr. Lemira's confidence so he can kill him easily. McGarrett must work out this plot and save the day before it is too late.

episodes.name: Time And Memories
episodes.overview: When a lawyer is murdered, his wife becomes the top suspect and McGarrett investigates. However, matters are complicated by the fact that the woman had a relationship with McGarrett, and he jeopardises his job because of this.

episodes.name: The Guarnerius Caper
episodes.overview: Shortly after giving a recital, the violin of a visiting Russian virtuoso is stolen, and McGarrett must retrieve it before the theft turns into an international incident.

episodes.name: The Ransom
episodes.overview: Five-O's efforts to rescue a young boy from kidnappers go wrong when Kono is captured and beaten. An angry McGarrett must work out a way to rescue Kono without further endangering him.

episodes.name: Force Of Waves
episodes.overview: When a ruthless businessman is blown up in a boat explosion, Five-O has many suspects to choose from, and they use psychological methods to determine the guilty party.

episodes.name: The Reunion
episodes.overview: A Japanese computer research company executive is recognised by a veteran as his former captor in a Phillippine prison camp in World War II.

episodes.name: The Late John Louisiana
episodes.overview: The hitman sent to kill the witness to a two year old murder instead falls in love with her and McGarrett and the team must lead the search to find her before duty overtakes love.

episodes.name: The Last Eden
episodes.overview: Five-O search for the criminals who have set up Hawaiian singer and ecologist Jimmy Nuanu as the fall guy for a sewage plant bombing.

episodes.name: Over Fifty? Steal!
episodes.overview: McGarrett and company must pit their wits against a veteran thief and robber who leaves Monopoly money at the scene of his crimes.

episodes.name: Beautiful Screamer
episodes.overview: Dan Williams's fiancee is murdered by a strangler who writes poetry in lipstick on his victims' legs. Danno resolves to catch the culprit who has other murderous plans to carry out.

episodes.name: The Payoff
episodes.overview: McGarrett must apprehend two abductors who are on the run with the proceeds of their crime in order to protect the lives of their co-conspirators.

episodes.name: The Double Wall
episodes.overview: When a convicted murderer, Harry Kellem, hears a dying man say he committed the crime that Kellem was jailed for, he takes a doctor hostage and McGarrett must negotiate his way out of the situation.

episodes.name: Paniolo
episodes.overview: A cowboy fears the loss of his land to a crooked estate agent and accidentally kills him by hitting him. McGarrett and his team must track the cowboy into the mountains and persuade him to give himself up.

episodes.name: Ten Thousand Diamonds And A Heart
episodes.overview: An electronics genius is busted out of prison so he can mastermind a massive robbery of diamonds from the Honolulu Diamond Exchange.

episodes.name: To Kill Or Be Killed
episodes.overview: Five-O investigates the death of Vietnam hero Jack Rigney, who fell from a balcony. His father is a World War II veteran, but his brother Michael is a peacenik, and Danno goes undercover as a draft dodger to help solve the mystery of Jack's death.

episodes.name: F.O.B. Honolulu (1)
episodes.overview: Wo Fat and other top international agents converge on Hawaii to place bids on printing plates for twenty dollar bills, which are in the possession of a former friend of McGarrett.

episodes.name: F.O.B. Honolulu (2)
episodes.overview: Five-O must deal with treason, murder and double-crosses in order to solve the case and prevent the U.S. from being flooded by fake currency.

episodes.name: The Gunrunner
episodes.overview: The wife of an arms dealer is kidnapped by revolutionaries who want the guns diverted from their original destination, but the arms dealer himself is not as innocent as matters would indicateâ€¦

episodes.name: Dear Enemy
episodes.overview: The wife of a convicted man fakes evidence in a new crime so that McGarrett will have to re-open her husband's case.

episodes.name: The Bomber And Mrs. Moroney
episodes.overview: Danno's past comes back to haunt him when the brother of a young boy he shot is released and wants revenge. The brother takes Chin Ho, Jenny and others hostage in McGarrett's office and threatens to blow them up, and Danno must resolve the tense situation.

episodes.name: The Grandstand Play (1)
episodes.overview: A baseball player, Lon Phillips, brings his backward son to Hawaii to escape threats on his life on the mainland.

episodes.name: The Grandstand Play (2)
episodes.overview: The son of the baseball player becomes the vital witness in a murder, but he is reluctant to tell either his father or Five-O of the crime.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview: The third season of Hawaii Five-O, an American television series, began September 16, 1970, and ended on March 10, 1971. It aired on CBS. The region 1 DVD was released on January 22, 2008.

episodes.name: Highest Castle, Deepest Grave
episodes.overview: A ten year old case is reopened when an archaeological dig unearths the skeletons of two murder victims.

episodes.name: No Bottles... No Cans... No People
episodes.overview: Gangster Johnny Oporta arranges for his enemies to be murdered and then covers up his crimes by incinerating their bodies. McGarrett and the others must stop this murderous spree.

episodes.name: Wednesday, Ladies Free
episodes.overview: Vic Tanaka is murdering women and painting their faces to resemble a prostitute he once knew, who is now happily married. McGarrett and his team must find the killer before he does any more damage.

episodes.name: 3,000 Crooked Miles To Honolulu
episodes.overview: Five-O is up against a sophisticated gang who have come to Hawaii to cash $750,000 of traveller's cheques.

episodes.name: Two Doves And Mr. Heron
episodes.overview: A hippie robs an embezzler of the key to a locker containing $250,000. Meanwhile, Danno is trying to contact the daughter of his Berkeley University landlady, who happens to be the hippie's girlfriendâ€¦

episodes.name: ...And I Want Some Candy And A Gun That Shoots
episodes.overview: Young Vietnam veteran and marksman Billy Shem Jr. buys a rifle under false pretences and proceeds to a bunker at Diamond Head. He then takes pot shots at the people on the road and then the police who arrive. McGarrett must neutralise the threat he poses by any means possible.

episodes.name: Air Cargo -- Dial For Murder
episodes.overview: While investigating the death of a security agent at an airport, McGarrett comes into contact with a gang who hijack cargo.

episodes.name: For A Million... Why Not?
episodes.overview: Five seemingly good citizens with different motives band together to steal $6,000,000 while McGarrett is away on Maui at a trial.

episodes.name: The Burning Ice
episodes.overview: McGarrett finds holes in a convict's story and a husband becomes a suspect in the murder of his wife.

episodes.name: Rest In Peace, Somebody
episodes.overview: A policeman who was kicked off the force blames McGarrett and Five-O and plans to kill the Governor.

episodes.name: A Matter Of Mutual Concern
episodes.overview: McGarrett must deal with the conflicts between four gangs of differing ethnic background, and try to uncover illegal activities.

episodes.name: Nine, Ten -- You're Dead
episodes.overview: A mob boss seeks revenge on a former boxer who smashed the hand of a novice to prevent him from ending up ruining his life in the boxing ring.

episodes.name: Is This Any Way To Run A Paradise?
episodes.overview: McGarrett and the team must find out who is behind a series of ecological stunts, when it is feared that a company executive will be their next target.

episodes.name: Odd Man In
episodes.overview: A veteran criminal who has already had dealings with Five-O escapes, and plans to steal millions of dollars from drug smugglers.

episodes.name: Bait Once, Bait Twice
episodes.overview: A woman attempts suicide in order to get her boyfriend to come out into the open and expose himself to an assassination attempt.

episodes.name: The Ninety-Second War (1)
episodes.overview: McGarrett is framed in an elaborate set up by Wo Fat, and has to contend with a foreign double amongst other problems.

episodes.name: The Ninety-Second War (2)
episodes.overview: Several faces from the past reappear as McGarrett must stop Wo Fat from carrying out his plan, a ninety second attack on a missile tracking base.

episodes.name: Skinhead
episodes.overview: When a young woman is beaten and raped and a soldier is arrested for the crime, McGarrett begins to have doubts about his guilt.

episodes.name: While You're At It, Bring In The Moon
episodes.overview: An eccentric billionaire is accused of murdering a business associate, but will not leave his boat to defend himself against the accusations, allowing his associates to declare him mentally incompetent.

episodes.name: Cloth Of Gold
episodes.overview: Three real estate crooks die horrible and mysterious shellfish related deaths, and McGarrett and the others must establish the link between them, and who has reason to want them dead.

episodes.name: Good Night, Baby - Time To Die!
episodes.overview: McGarrett sets up a cordon of police around a young woman to capture her boyfriend who has escaped from jail, but all is not as it seemsâ€¦

episodes.name: Didn't We Meet At A Murder?
episodes.overview: A young widow becomes part of a blackmail plot involving the murder of a Chicago mobster.

episodes.name: Follow The White Brick Road
episodes.overview: Danno goes undercover onboard a Navy ship to try and uncover how sailors are smuggling heroin onto the islands.

episodes.name: R&R -- &R
episodes.overview: A psychotic man named Ralston is killing the wives of members of his army unit, and Five-O, including Kono on his last case, must stop him before he commits any more crazed attacks.

4.name: Season 4
4.overview: The fourth season of Hawaii Five-O, an American television series, began September 14, 1971, and ended on March 7, 1972. It aired on CBS. The region 1 DVD was released on June 10, 2008.

episodes.name: Death Is A Company Policy
episodes.overview: A local thug, Piro Manoa, is trying to create the impression of corruption in the Five-O force, and Duke is implicated in a murder. McGarrett and the team, with new recruit Ben Kokua, must save Duke's position and work out the plot of the organisation behind the false accusations.

episodes.name: Death Wish On Tantalus Mountain
episodes.overview: When two of a egotistical racing driver's support staff are murdered, suspicions of sabotage fall upon his attractive girlfriend.

episodes.name: You Don't Have To Kill To Get Rich -- But It Helps.
episodes.overview: A private investigator, Sam Tolliver, arrives from Texas to help an old friend who is being blackmailed and is at risk of being killed if he doesn't pay up, but he ends up wanting to become part of the blackmail operation.

episodes.name: Pig In A Blanket
episodes.overview: Danno shoots an apparently armed teenager but finds that he was mistaken, and public opinion and the teen's brother turn against him. McGarrett must act to defuse the potentially explosive situation.

episodes.name: The Jinn Who Clears The Way
episodes.overview: Wo Fat is suspected of being behind the theft of a mobile ICBM device, and McGarrett with other top officials must stop him selling it off to the highest bidder.

episodes.name: Fools Die Twice
episodes.overview: Army computer technician Jack Gulley kidnaps a scientist and then uses a planned heist by three accomplices on a military base to divert Five-O's attention from his sale of the scientist to the highest bidder.

episodes.name: Chain Of Events
episodes.overview: A doctor tracking venereal disease is murdered, and Five-O must track the series of encounters to find out who is a carrier. Their investigation is made doubly important by the murder of a young woman who is close to a upcoming politician. He seems a likely suspect but McGarrett suspects a deeper plot.

episodes.name: Journey Out Of Limbo
episodes.overview: Danno is found in the back of a truck, dazed and confused, and McGarrett and the others must help him piece together how he came to be in that situation.

episodes.name: 'V' For Vashon: The Son (1)
episodes.overview: McGarrett becomes involved with the Vashon mafioso family after the youngest member, Chris, is implicated in a daring raid on a hotel.

episodes.name: 'V' For Vashon: The Father (2)
episodes.overview: McGarrett must contend with Honore Vashon, who wants revenge for his son's death.

episodes.name: 'V' For Vashon: The Patriarch (3)
episodes.overview: Dominick Vashon, the patriarch of the clan, makes his attempt to bring down McGarrett and Five-O.

episodes.name: The Clock Struck Twelve
episodes.overview: When McGarrett arrests a group of vigilante nationalists, hidden bombs at the courthouse threaten to destabilise the islands.

episodes.name: I'm A Family Crook -- Don't Shoot!
episodes.overview: A husband and wife team of scam merchants get caught between some of Hawaii's most powerful mobs.

episodes.name: The Child Stealers
episodes.overview: Two drifters, Gar and Nina, steal children and sell them on to a mainland adoption agency in order to raise the cash to buy a boat and go cruising.

episodes.name: Thanks For The Honeymoon
episodes.overview: McGarrett agrees to let Toni, a tough female convict, get married and have a honeymoon in protective custody as long as she will testify against a local hood.

episodes.name: The Listener
episodes.overview: A crazed electronics wizard threatens the lives of a psychiatrist and his patients by using electronic devices and gadgets.

episodes.name: Here Today, Gone Tonight
episodes.overview: Five-O has a suspect for a murder, but they have one problem. How can the suspect have been in two places at the same time?

episodes.name: The Odd Lot Caper
episodes.overview: A senior partner in a stock exchange firm comes up with a foolproof plan to rob the Honolulu Stock Exchange.

episodes.name: Will The Real Mr. Winkler Please Die?
episodes.overview: McGarrett and company must break through a tissue of lies in order to protect a Russian defector from being killed.

episodes.name: Little Girl Blue
episodes.overview: Two simple criminals kidnap a young girl, and hide out in a bunker at Diamond Head. McGarrett must unravel the reason why they are there and get the girl safely away from them.

episodes.name: Percentage
episodes.overview: A travel agent who operates gambling trips is killed in order to send a warning to others that the syndicates will not tolerate competition.

episodes.name: Engaged To Be Buried
episodes.overview: Chin Ho must face the fact that his daughter, Alia, is in love with the son of a local criminal under investigation, and that she plans to get married to him.

episodes.name: The Diamond That Nobody Stole
episodes.overview: A burglary at the home of a well known island family sets off a series of events that ends in murder.

episodes.name: Jury Of One
episodes.overview: A single person is holding out in a Five-O trial, and McGarrett and the team have to find out who is stalling and why they are doing it.

5.name: Season 5
5.overview: The fifth season of Hawaii Five-O premiered on September 12, 1972 and ended March 13, 1973. 24 episodes aired during this season. The Region 1 DVD was released on November 18, 2008.

episodes.name: Hookman
episodes.overview: A amputee with no hands sets out to kill every police officer who contributed to his injury, and that includes Steve McGarrett.

episodes.name: Draw Me A Killer
episodes.overview: Murders are being committed seemingly at random every six weeks, and McGarrett is at a loss to understand the motives for these crimes. However, a newspaper may hold the answer.

episodes.name: Charter For Death
episodes.overview: When a large amount of diseased rats are found on a boat with all the crew dead, Five-O must contend with an outbreak of bubonic plague.

episodes.name: One Big Happy Family
episodes.overview: A family of white-trash mass killers arrive on Hawaii after wreaking a trail of devastation on the mainland, and McGarrett must catch them before they can do more damage on the islands.

episodes.name: The Sunday Torch
episodes.overview: Buildings are being set on fire on Sundays, and a known firebug is the top suspect. However, McGarrett begins to think that others may be responsible.

episodes.name: Murder Is A Taxing Affair
episodes.overview: A corrupt federal agent who is tracking a man under indictment for tax evasion kills him for the $600,000 he is carrying, and then loses the money.

episodes.name: Tricks Are Not Treats
episodes.overview: The killing of an important pimp threatens an all out war between two competing vice empires.

episodes.name: Why Wait Till Uncle Kevin Dies?
episodes.overview: A string of five murders of wealthy men leads McGarrett to a crooked inheritance scheme.

episodes.name: Flash Of Color, Flash Of Death
episodes.overview: A glamorous woman sets up an opal smuggler so her accomplices can rob both the smuggler and a jewellery store at the same time.

episodes.name: A Bullet For El Diablo
episodes.overview: A dictator must evade a female assassin sent to kill him, one that looks just like his own daughter.

episodes.name: The Finishing Touch
episodes.overview: McGarrett brings in a document expert to help him crack a case involving forged government securities, but he soon becomes suspicious of the expert as wellâ€¦

episodes.name: Anybody Can Build A Bomb
episodes.overview: A nuclear scientist becomes involved in an extortion plot when a gang threaten to explode a small nuclear weapon somewhere in Honolulu.

episodes.name: Try To Die On Time
episodes.overview: Harry Foxton, a gambler, is himself the subject of huge bets over what hour he will die. McGarrett must work out the gambler's complex relationships to get to the bottom of this case.

episodes.name: The $100,000 Nickel
episodes.overview: A thief known for using sleight-of-hand is hired to steal a valuable nickel, but the coin ends up on a journey across many miles and through many hands.

episodes.name: The Flip Side Is Death
episodes.overview: A mock military emergency leaves a bank open for a robbery, and Five-O must travel to the opposite side of Oahu to find out more in their investigation.

episodes.name: The Banzai Pipeline
episodes.overview: An exciting surf beach is the location for a filming session, where a man catches a killer on camera.

episodes.name: One Born Every Minute
episodes.overview: A pair of crooks team up with local criminals and use phony diamonds as bait to prey on wealthy male tourists. McGarrett and Five-O must shut off this sinister racket.

episodes.name: Secret Witness
episodes.overview: A young man witnesses a murder, and finds himself and his family are now the killer's targets.

episodes.name: Death With Father
episodes.overview: The son of a Federal Narcotics officer becomes involved in a heroin refining operation.

episodes.name: Murder With A Golden Touch
episodes.overview: When a man is found dead with gold dust on him, McGarrett and his team must investigate where the stolen gold came from and how it is being bought onto the market.

episodes.name: Nightmare In Blue
episodes.overview: A series of rapes and murders occur, and the main suspect seems to be a police officer...

episodes.name: Mother's Deadly Helper
episodes.overview: A right-wing crackpot, Cord McKenzie, metes out â€˜justice' to people who have been found innocent on technicalities or released early. He thinks he is helping the police, but McGarrett thinks otherwise.

episodes.name: Killer At Sea
episodes.overview: While investigating a robbery and kidnapping, the trail of clues leads McGarrett and the team to an ocean liner with a deadly passenger.

episodes.name: 30,000 Rooms And I Have The Key
episodes.overview: An aging jewel thief steals from rooms at Waikiki hotels, and taunts Five-O by leaving a trail of clues behind.

6.name: Season 6
6.overview:
The sixth season of Hawaii Five-O premiered on September 11, 1973 and ended February 26, 1974. 24 episodes aired during this season. The Region 1 DVD was released on April 21, 2009.

Creator and executive producer Leonard Freeman died during this season.

episodes.name: The Young Assassins
episodes.overview: Danno and a college professor are kidnapped by a revolutionary group of young radicals led by a hardened criminal.

episodes.name: A Hawaiian Nightmare
episodes.overview: A geophysics expert, Bernard Brown, is heavily in debt, so he comes up with a plan to cause an explosion in the Hawaii Volcanoes National Park, which will cause lava to pour all down the hillside and into the city of Hilo, unless the Governor comes up with half a million dollars as a ransom.

episodes.name: I'll Kill 'Em Again
episodes.overview: Eddie Josephs is a paranoid schizophrenic who is carrying out murders based on old Five-O cases. McGarrett must follow his clues and catch him before more people die.

episodes.name: Steal Now -- Pay Later
episodes.overview: A sophisticated thief is selling his goods to legitimate businessmen, and Five-O must find a way of trapping him.

episodes.name: Bomb, Bomb, Who's Got The Bomb?
episodes.overview: Senator Harlan Henderson suffers from multiple personalities, and one side of him wants to kill himself. However, he ends up blowing up his secretary, and McGarrett uses handwriting and a diagnosis from a psychiatrist to try to crack the case.

episodes.name: Right Grave, Wrong Body
episodes.overview: A criminal, Hobart, is robbing liquor stores using a policeman's former gun, but the officer wants it back as he used it to kill a bankrobber five years before and the body has been uncovered.

episodes.name: We Hang Our Own
episodes.overview: When his son is beaten to death, a powerful cattle baron takes matters into his own hands, and McGarrett and Five-O must prevent the rule of law from breaking down.

episodes.name: The Two-Faced Corpse
episodes.overview: A gangland execution investigation takes a turn for the peculiar when it is found that the victim had two identities.

episodes.name: How To Steal A Masterpiece
episodes.overview: Five-O must investigate why three infallible security systems are failing to prevent the theft of priceless artworks.

episodes.name: A Gun For McGarrett
episodes.overview: After an attempt is made on Steve McGarrett's life, he is drawn towards a female art dealer, but she too may not be good for his healthâ€¦

episodes.name: Welcome To Our Branch Office
episodes.overview: Two conmen use a gang of Five-O lookalikes and doubles to extort money from Honolulu businessmen.

episodes.name: Presenting... In The Center Ring... Murder
episodes.overview: Wo Fat returns to Hawaii in order to have a Chinese diplomat whom he classes as a foolish peace-maker assassinated.

episodes.name: Hara-Kiri: Murder
episodes.overview: McGarrett and Five-O need to find out why a Japanese banker ritually killed himself and catch a true criminal into the bargain.

episodes.name: Bones Of Contention
episodes.overview: A Honolulu murder is mysteriously linked to a human fossil smuggled out of China in the Second World War.

episodes.name: Computer Killer
episodes.overview: An investigation into a murder is sent off track through the modification of computer information, and Five-O must use the latest technology to rescue the case.

episodes.name: A Woman's Work Is With A Gun
episodes.overview: Three women desperately in need of money take to armed robbery of tourist buses as a way to raise some quick cash.

episodes.name: Small Witness, Large Crime
episodes.overview: When a young boy is arrested as a witness to a murder, McGarrett must contend with a fiery deputy public prosecutor.

episodes.name: Ring Of Life
episodes.overview: A million dollar reward for the return of five figurines sparks off a trail of murder and theft that leads to Hawaii.

episodes.name: Study In Rage
episodes.overview: When a psychotic man kills his doctor, Five-O must use a unfinished painting to gather clues to his whereabouts.

episodes.name: And The Horse Jumped Over The Moon
episodes.overview: An elaborate sea and air scheme for heroin smuggling goes unnoticed until one of the gang tries to sell out their plan for a fix of heroin.

episodes.name: Hit Gun For Sale
episodes.overview: McGarrett must prevent a mob war by tracking down an unknown hitman and his intended target.

episodes.name: The Hostage
episodes.overview: When a deranged ex-Army officer shoots a policeman and takes a young girl hostage, McGarrett disagrees with a police captain over the best way to free her.

episodes.name: Diary Of A Gun
episodes.overview: A Saturday Night Special passes from person to person and causes Five-O trouble and others misery.

episodes.name: 6,000 Deadly Tickets
episodes.overview: Five-O works with a air traffic investigator in order to put a stop to illegal ticket sales which have already cost several lives.

episodes.name: Murder - Eyes Only (1)
episodes.overview: When a letter bomb kills a Naval Officer whilst McGarrett is on Navy Duty, he is called upon to investigate and uncovers a plot involving an old nemesis...

episodes.name: Murder - Eyes Only (2)
episodes.overview: McGarrett must try his utmost to foil Wo Fat's plans which include hostages and brainwashing.

episodes.name: McGarrett Is Missing
episodes.overview: McGarrett must again face mobster Charlie Bombay when a plane carrying them to Honolulu crashes in the forests.

episodes.name: Termination With Extreme Prejudice
episodes.overview: A British agent, Harry Wells, arrives in Hawaii in pursuit of a turncoat, but not all is what it seems for Five-O...

episodes.name: Target? The Lady
episodes.overview: Five-O must find a female courier who witnessed a murder before a hitman can...

episodes.name: Death's Name Is Sam
episodes.overview: A road accident starts the trail towards a plot to use SAM missiles to bring down a VIP jet plane.

episodes.name: The Case Against McGarrett
episodes.overview: McGarrett offers himself as a hostage exchange, but is then put on 'trial' by Honore Vashon.

episodes.name: The Defector
episodes.overview: McGarrett meets his match in Dr. Grant Ormsbee, a grumpy and aggravating scientist who is sheltering a suspected Chinese defector.

episodes.name: Sing A Song Of Suspense
episodes.overview: When a singer witnesses a murder committed by a racketeer, Five-O has to protect her until she can give evidence, but this is not an easy job...

episodes.name: Retire In Sunny Hawaii -- Forever
episodes.overview: Danno's Aunt Clara becomes acquainted with a man on the plane to Honolulu, but becomes concerned about him afterwards. Dan, Steve and the others ignore her at first, but then the man turns up dead...

episodes.name: How To Steal A Submarine
episodes.overview: A vice-principal enlists the help of his students and a submarine to smuggle drugs.

episodes.name: The Waterfront Steal
episodes.overview: When Five-O fail to prevent a series of thefts at dockside warehouses, an influential owner creates trouble for McGarrett.

episodes.name: Honor Is An Unmarked Grave
episodes.overview: A writer who specialises in solving mysteries uncovers the body in a seven year old case, but it raises more questions than it answers...

episodes.name: A Touch Of Guilt
episodes.overview: Three boys commit a gang rape on a waitress, but one is the son of a Senator and the crime is covered up...

episodes.name: Wooden Model Of A Rat
episodes.overview: Whilst trying to stop the smuggling of small Oriental animal statues, McGarrett is caught illegally in possession of one of them as part of his personal collection.

episodes.name: Deadly Persuasion
episodes.overview: A disturbed young man steals nerve gas to use against a visiting royal family as revenge for the death of his father.

episodes.name: Legacy Of Terror
episodes.overview: When an elderly importer who was a World War II Japanese spy is killed, Five-O seeks his killer.

episodes.name: Loose Ends Get Hit
episodes.overview: A clear cut murder case against an island mobster is derailed due to McGarrett.

episodes.name: Anatomy Of A Bribe
episodes.overview: A crooked contractor and a buildings inspector are under suspicion after the new Global Trade Center in Honolulu goes up in flames.

episodes.name: Turkey Shoot At Makapuu
episodes.overview: When an airline stewardess and a hang-gliding instructor are murdered, Five-O must find the killers.

episodes.name: A Killer Grows Wings
episodes.overview: Criminals threaten to use a special type of moth to wipe out the sugar cane on Hawaii and destroy the industry.

episodes.name: The Capsule Kidnapping
episodes.overview: The son of a Japanese businessman is kidnapped and held in a capsule underwater until a $1.5 million dollar ransom is paid...

episodes.name: Love Thy Neighbor -- Take His Wife
episodes.overview: Ben Tanaka, a well-known ecologist, seems to be behind the kidnapping of a wealthy land developer's wife, but all is not as it seems and a conspiracy gradually reveals itself.

episodes.name: A Sentence To Steal
episodes.overview: McGarrett sends an undercover agent into a rehabilitation home for juvenile offenders to find out who is behind the theft of gold from dental supply warehouses.

episodes.name: Nine Dragons (1)
episodes.overview: When Wo Fat steals toxins in an attempt to take out the leaders of Communist China, McGarrett must track him to Hong Kong.

episodes.name: Nine Dragons (2)
episodes.overview: In Hong Kong, Steve is caught by Wo Fat and mentally and physically tortured by being 'reconditioned'. He must beat these problems to save the day again.

episodes.name: Assault On The Palace
episodes.overview: McGarrett must solve a daring bank robbery committed during the King Kamehameha Day Parade under the cover of a historic re-enactment.

episodes.name: Oldest Profession -- Latest Price
episodes.overview: The murder of island prostitutes seems to be linked to an extortion racketeer who is determined to make a return...

episodes.name: Man On Fire
episodes.overview: Five bodies are found in the crater of Mauna Loa contaminated by radiation from illegal plutonium, and Five-O must find and confiscate this deadly toxin.

episodes.name: Tour De Force, Killer Aboard
episodes.overview: Two seemingly unconnected deaths lead McGarrett into a desperate race to prevent the assassination of a visiting Sheikh.

episodes.name: The Last Of The Great Paperhangers
episodes.overview: A masterful forger plans a massive robbery of Navy funds, and McGarrett is made to look rather inept...

episodes.name: Heads, You're Dead
episodes.overview: When yacht racers are found dead on their craft, Five-O launches a desperate search for high-seas buccaneers.

episodes.name: Let Death Do Us Part
episodes.overview: A escaped convict may well have a strong case of innocence, when Five-O become involved in the paranormal...

episodes.name: Double Exposure
episodes.overview: A press photographer is pursued relentlessly after she takes a photo of a supposedly dead gangster who has returned to the islands to take control of the local syndicate.

episodes.name: Yes, My Deadly Daughter
episodes.overview: When $10 million goes missing from a crimelord, the culprit seems to be dangerously close to home...

episodes.name: Target -- A Cop
episodes.overview: Police are being lured into traps and shot, and Five-O have difficulty nailing a suspect when their primary lead turns out to be a paraplegic.

episodes.name: The Bells Toll At Noon
episodes.overview: The boyfriend of an overdose victim re-enacts famous film murders in a revenge on all the people he sees as responsible.

episodes.name: Man In A Steel Frame
episodes.overview: McGarrett is the top suspect in the murder of his girlfriend, and the evidence against him is seemingly overwhelming...

episodes.name: Ready... Aim...
episodes.overview: Five-O must work with a Japanese officer to find the source of handsguns that are flooding the black market in Tokyo.

episodes.name: Elegy In A Rain Forest
episodes.overview: The daughter of Attorney General John Manicote is kidnapped by a deranged rapist and murderer, and Steve must not only contend with the criminal but Manicote's emotional state as well...

episodes.name: Dealer's Choice -- Blackmail
episodes.overview: A hit and run incident leads Five-O to a gambling syndicate and Officer Welles's brother.

episodes.name: A Capitol Crime
episodes.overview: A pensioner threatens to blow himself and his hostages up if he doesn't stop the demolition of his home.

episodes.name: To Die In Paradise
episodes.overview: A lady singer is kidnapped and it looks as if her and her captors have died at sea...

episodes.name: Blood Money Is Hard To Wash
episodes.overview: A gangster attempts to buy an interest in a football club so that he can launder money through it.

episodes.name: To Kill A Mind
episodes.overview: While searching for parts from a sunken Soviet submarine, McGarrett become suspicious about the particular parts that are being recovered.

episodes.name: Requiem For A Saddle-Bronc Rider
episodes.overview: A missing rodeo cowboy and the murder of a young couple pose a puzzling mystery for Five-O.

episodes.name: See How She Runs
episodes.overview: The daughter of a LA detective and friend of McGarrett is framed for murder and then joins a cult.

episodes.name: Practical Jokes Can Kill You
episodes.overview: A gang of thieves steal army rifles by peculiar means - hang-gliding into the armoury!

episodes.name: Up The Rebels
episodes.overview: An Irish terrorist uses disguise and deception in order to be able to smuggle explosives for the Troubles.

episodes.name: You Don't See Many Pirates These Days
episodes.overview: When a sea-freighter is hijacked, the wealthy millionaire owner calls in Five-O, but all is not how it seems...

episodes.name: The Cop On The Cover
episodes.overview: McGarrett must solve both a mysterious kidnapping and the problem of having a nosy reporter analysing his every move.

episodes.name: The Friends Of Joey Kalima
episodes.overview: McGarrett engages in a personal struggle to clear the record of an officer and close friend accused of criminal activity.

episodes.name: The Descent Of The Torches
episodes.overview: Five-O must find out whether the death of an archaeologist is linked to his supposed desecration of tomb of King Kamehameha.

episodes.name: The Ninth Step
episodes.overview: The return of a disgraced alcoholic policeman causes extra problems in the pursuit of a pair of armoured truck robbers.

episodes.name: Shake Hands With The Man On The Moon
episodes.overview: McGarrett must deal with an astronaut turned real-estate salesman in order to crack the case of a murdered reporter.

episodes.name: Deadly Doubles
episodes.overview: When a Russian tennis star wants to defect, McGarrett must work to prevent an international incident.

episodes.name: Deep Cover
episodes.overview: A secret submarine, the murder of a Navy officer and strange amnesia create a puzzling case for Steve McGarrett.

episodes.name: Tsunami
episodes.overview: A gang of university students plan a hoax tidal wave in order to steal priceless jewellery.

episodes.name: East Wind -- Ill Wind
episodes.overview: When an Asian ex-leader dies in a seemingly accidental swimming incident, his wife is convinced that he was murdered by forces from their home country.

episodes.name: Tread The King's Shadow
episodes.overview: McGarrett becomes involved in a love triangle between a young local man, a rich girl and her father who hates the Hawaiian origins of the boy.

episodes.name: The Big Aloha
episodes.overview: A young doctor is suspected of having been involved in the murder of his mentor.

episodes.name: A Short Walk On The Longshore
episodes.overview: In order to find out the identity of the murderer of a union leader, McGarrett goes undercover as a longshoreman.

episodes.name: The Silk Trap
episodes.overview: An up-and-coming young politician is blackmailed in order to affect his leadership of an congressional investigation.

episodes.name: Head To Head
episodes.overview: While pursuing a drug dealer, McGarrett also has to contend with a federal agent.

episodes.name: Tall On The Wave
episodes.overview: Danno must deal with a surfer, one of his friends, who is suspected of the murder of a girl.

episodes.name: Angel In Blue
episodes.overview: A female undercover cop threatens the progress of an investigation when she starts a relationship with a man connected to the case.

episodes.name: When Does A War End?
episodes.overview: A Japanese businessman comes under attack from a young man whose father suffered in an Japanese Prisoner of War camp.

episodes.name: Invitation To Murder
episodes.overview: McGarrett must deal with an apparent mass murderer when a will creates a fortune for the last family member left alive.

episodes.name: Frozen Assets
episodes.overview: A cryogenics institute comes under suspicion when an investigative writer becomes involved.

episodes.name: My Friend, The Enemy
episodes.overview: Five-O must deal with the kidnapping of an Arab princess, and Steve must also deal with an Italian female journalist's constant interruptions.

episodes.name: A Stranger In His Grave
episodes.overview: Five-O become involved in a complex case of body-switching, mystery investments and suitcases full of money.

episodes.name: A Death In The Family
episodes.overview: Five-O's world is shattered when mobsters catch Chin Ho undercover and order him to be killed.

episodes.name: The Sleeper
episodes.overview: After a government agent is murdered, McGarrett must identify the traitor in a scientific facility.

episodes.name: Horoscope For Murder
episodes.overview: When an astrologer visits McGarrett to inform him of a murderer with a terrible temper, his antagonism lessens when her assumptions seem to be partly true.

episodes.name: Deadly Courier
episodes.overview: An assassin who doesn't know he's an assassin? Sounds like a punch line from "The Naked Gun," but it's the story of this episode, where a diplomatic courier with a briefcase chained to his wrist is hypnotized and programmed to rig the case with a bomb. When Danno goes undercover to ferret out the assassination ring, he himself is brainwashed and programmed to kill McGarrett.

episodes.name: The Case Against Philip Christie
episodes.overview: McGarrett is the lone hold-out in a trial where the guilt of the accused seems certain.

episodes.name: Small Potatoes
episodes.overview: Steve is framed on the orders of a gambling syndicate, and becomes involved with a woman who is part of the case.

episodes.name: A Distant Thunder
episodes.overview: Five-O must deal with the plans of a Neo Nazi organisation to kill Bobby Tamara, the ""Hawaiian Kennedy"".

episodes.name: Death Mask
episodes.overview: When a street robber claims that he stole King Tutankhamun's mask for fun, McGarrett suspects there is more to the case than simple robbery.

episodes.name: The Pagoda Factor
episodes.overview: McGarrett assists a convict in his escape, so that he can go back to his gang and provide Five-O with inside information.

episodes.name: A Long Time Ago
episodes.overview: Danno is surprised when he bumps into a former flame and even more concerned when she seems to be involved in criminal activities.

episodes.name: Why Won't Linda Die?
episodes.overview: The death of a prominent politician reveals a strange love triangle.

episodes.name: The Miracle Man
episodes.overview: When a preacher is attacked by a man convinced that he is responsible for his wife's death, Five-O investigate more closely and discover some less than godly motives.

episodes.name: Number One With A Bullet (1)
episodes.overview: Two rival mobs attempt to take control of the disco scene in Honolulu.

episodes.name: Number One With A Bullet (2)
episodes.overview: The rival gangs are on the brink of all out war, and Five-O must struggle to stop them.

episodes.name: The Meighan Conspiracy
episodes.overview: When a robbed bank vault shows no signs of break-in, an inside job seems the likely solution. McGarrett's trail of clues leads him back to the builder of the vault and his wife...

episodes.name: The Spirit Is Willie
episodes.overview: Millicent Shand returns and claims that her niece's husband has faked his own death in order to get his hands on $500,000.

episodes.name: The Bark And The Bite
episodes.overview: A vacationing heiress seems unconcerned when McGarrett warns her that someone is after her ruby.

episodes.name: Stringer
episodes.overview: When a photographer takes a picture of a politician making a deal with an underworld figure, he tries blackmail. However, he is not prepared for the ruthless nature of the mobsters.

episodes.name: The Execution File
episodes.overview: A private detective is rescuing girls from prostitution, and using the opportunity to kill the pimps as well.

episodes.name: A Very Personal Matter
episodes.overview: When the son of one of Steve's friends dies of an overdose, he goes after a doctor that he suspects of over-prescribing drugs.

episodes.name: The Skyline Killer
episodes.overview: The hunt for a high-rise killer is made more difficult for Five-O when a journalist offers to share his profits in exchange for the killer's story.

episodes.name: The Year Of The Horse (1)
episodes.overview: When a woman dies due to heroin packets bursting inside her and the Governor is implicated, McGarrett and Danno head off to Singapore to discover a smuggling operation.

episodes.name: The Year Of The Horse (2)
episodes.overview: Five-O must close the heroin smuggling operation to exonerate the Governor and catch the figures behind the scheme.

episodes.name: A Lion In The Streets (1)
episodes.overview: McGarrett finds himself stymied when Hawaiian nationalists and local underworld mobsters clash over a union election.

episodes.name: A Lion In The Streets (2)
episodes.overview: Labouring under a ban on cooperation by native Hawaiians because of a Kahuna, McGarrett must try to prevent war on the streets...

episodes.name: Who Says Cops Don't Cry
episodes.overview: When the husband of a policewoman is gunned down by opportunist robbers, she resolves to catch them any way she can.

episodes.name: Though The Heavens Fall
episodes.overview: A group of high society men set out to see that justice is done - the catch being that it is justice on their terms only...

episodes.name: Sign Of The Ram
episodes.overview: Jessica Humboldt, an astrologer and friend of Agnes DuBois, comes to McGarrett with news that a forthcoming match will be disastrous for a boxer. McGarrett must overcome his suspicions and crack the case.

episodes.name: Good Help Is Hard To Find
episodes.overview: Tony Alika and Guido Marioni, killer of Kimo's family, together hatch a plot to frame and embarrass the Five-O team by making them look stupid or corrupt.

episodes.name: Image Of Fear
episodes.overview: When a woman is stalked by a strange figure, she seems to be seeing things and her friends are worried as to her mental health. However, events prove her case and an accomplice is revealed...

episodes.name: Use A Gun, Go To Hell
episodes.overview: When two surfer bums use a gun to rob a shop, it starts off a trail of death and misery involving children, politics and blackmail.

episodes.name: Voice Of Terror
episodes.overview: A group of terrorists capture a female officer and use her to further their aims, and McGarrett and the team must find a way to take them out without endangering the life of Officer Dean.

episodes.name: A Shallow Grave
episodes.overview: A young man on vacation has strange visions that lead him to the site of an old murder and help him discover a lost family.

episodes.name: The Kahuna
episodes.overview: When two healthy young people die mysteriously, local traditions prevent post mortems, and a strange conspiracy is gradually uncovered when Truck seems to fall under the power of a Kahuna...

episodes.name: Labyrinth
episodes.overview: When a rich socialite is kidnapped, her husband insists that Five-O stay out of the case. However, his reasons may not all be on the level as events take a series of twists and turns...

episodes.name: School For Assassins
episodes.overview: McGarrett and Kimo must stop a gang of trained assassins from disrupting a meeting of energy ministers.

episodes.name: For Old Times Sake
episodes.overview: A aging crook decides to use dollar bill printing plates he made to raise cash for a charity, but he fails to realise the trouble that this will cause.

episodes.name: The Golden Noose
episodes.overview: McGarrett is suspicious of an aide who arrives in Hawaii to retrieve millions of dollars held in trust for a Southern Asian state and he must prevent a daring gold robbery.

episodes.name: The Flight Of The Jewels
episodes.overview: A gang of clever students use radio-controlled planes to execute the theft of Queen Liliokalani's jewels.

episodes.name: Clash Of Shadows
episodes.overview: The murder of a Nazi-hunter and discovery of a World War II medal set McGarrett and the team on the trail of a Nazi war criminal living in Honolulu...

episodes.name: A Bird In Hand...
episodes.overview: A group of seemingly harmless birdwatchers are the target of a vendetta. Five-O must discover why they were a target and stop any further violence.

episodes.name: The Moroville Covenant
episodes.overview: A politician trying for the Senate is weakened by the murder of the man who is blackmailing him.

episodes.name: Woe To Wo Fat
episodes.overview: The series concludes with the final showdown between McGarrett and Wo Fat. Three scientists have gone missing. They have one thing in common: they all attended a symposium that discussed a possible space-based, laser defense system. McGarrett impersonates a fourth scientist, Dr. Elton Raintree, who attended the same gathering and is soon abducted. Wo Fat is behind it all and wants the scientists to complete their work and produce such a device.
